{{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> |name = Return to Modesty: Discovering the Lost Virtue |image = A Return to Modesty.jpg |caption= |author = [[Wendy Shalit]] |cover_artist = |country = United States |language = English |genre = |publisher = Touchstone |release_date = 1999 |media_type = Print ([[Hardcover|Hardback]] & [[Paperback]]) |pages = 291 |isbn = 0684863170 }} '''''Return to Modesty: Discovering the Lost Virtue''''' is a [[1999 in literature|1999]] [[non-fiction]] debut [[book]] by [[Wendy Shalit]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=March 7, 1999|title=Maids of Honor|first=Emily|last=Eakin|url=https://www.nytimes.com/books/99/03/07/reviews/990307.07eakint.html}}</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/books/first/s/shalit-modesty.html The New York Times]</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2005/01/30/books/review/up-front.html The New York Times]</ref><ref>[http://www.plantinga.ca/m/MBM.HTM Plantinga.ca]</ref>
==Overview== A non-fiction book that claims the power to heal women's purported ills lies in reinstatement of sexual modesty, resurrection of romantic ideals, and conservative manners.
