* '''William Curtin''': Founder and Owner of Weapons & Effects, Novato, Ca.: Film Credits include ''[[Born on the Fourth of July (film)|Born on the Fourth of July]]'', ''[[Outbreak (film)|Outbreak]]'', ''[[Sniper (1993 film)|Sniper]]'', ''[[Forrest Gump|Forest Gump]]'', ''[[Windtalkers]]'', ''[[The Hunted (1995 film)|The Hunted]]'', ''[[Desert Heat (film)|Desert Heat]]'', ''[[Dead Presidents]]'', ''[[Anna and the King]]'', ''[[Metro (1997 film)|Metro]]'', ''[[Midnight Caller]]'', ''[[Nash Bridges]]'' and 2007-2018 as a Subject Matter Expert with the U.S. Dept. of Defense (DOD) in Ex-Soviet/COMBLOC Crew Served and Individual Weapon Systems Along with 20+ years Firearm Manufacturer for 20+ Law Enforcement Agencies. Also a California Class 1 Pyrotechnician and High Explosives Manufacturer for the DOD and Film Industry.
* '''Michael Papac''': Founder of Cinema Weaponry; film credits include the ''[[Lethal Weapon (franchise)|Lethal Weapon]]'' and ''[[Die Hard (film series)|Die Hard]]'' series, ''[[Three Kings (1999 film)|Three Kings]]'', ''[[We Were Soldiers]]'', ''[[Red (2010 film)|Red]]'', ''[[Terminator 3: Rise of the Machines]]'', and ''[[xXx (film)|xXx]]''.<ref name="Barrett2013">{{cite book|last=Barrett|first=Paul M.|title=Glock: The Rise of America's Gun|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sPNAkiAnm7cC&pg=PA72|date=15 January 2013|publisher=Broadway Books|isbn=978-0-307-71995-9|pages=70–72}}</ref>
* '''Mike Gibbons''': Founder of Gibbons, Ltd.; film credits include ''[[RoboCop 3]]'', ''[[Collateral (film)|Collateral]]'' and ''[[The A-Team (film)|The A-Team]]''.<ref name="JolliffeJones2004">{{cite book|last1=Jolliffe|first1=Genevieve|last2=Jones|first2=Chris|title=The Guerilla Film Makers Handbook: (US Edition)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zID5Ki711TsC&pg=PA344|date=27 April 2004|publisher=Continuum|isbn=978-0-8264-1464-9|page=344}}</ref>
* '''Gary Harper''': Owner of Harperhaus Weapons FX and authorized Armorer for ISS, credits include the ''[[Flags of our Fathers]]'', ''[[Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World]]'', "[[Raid on Son Tay]]", [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] series ''[[Deadliest Warrior]]'' and ''[[Rambo III]]''.<ref name="Ermey2005">{{cite book|last=Ermey|first=Lee|authorlink=Lee Ermey|title=Mail Call|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SQC-nOEiF-EC|date=12 January 2005|publisher=Hyperion Books|isbn=978-1-4013-0779-0|page=18}}</ref>
* '''Thell Reed''': Former World Champion live ammo quick-draw artist, now a freelance gun coach and weapons armorer in Hollywood; film credits include ''[[Tombstone (film)|Tombstone]]'', ''[[L.A. Confidential (film)|L.A. Confidential]]'', ''[[Blade (film)|Blade]]'', and ''[[Mr. & Mrs. Smith (2005 film)|Mr. & Mrs. Smith]]''.<ref name="Muir2004">{{cite book|last=Muir|first=John Kenneth|title=The Unseen Force: The Films of Sam Raimi|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QcgQuCURvGgC&pg=PA183|year=2004|publisher=Applause Theatre & Cinema Books|isbn=978-1-55783-607-6|page=183}}</ref>
* '''Syd Stembridge''': Former owner of Stembridge Gun Rentals, founded in 1903; film credits include the ''[[Rambo (film series)|Rambo]]'' series and ''[[Waterworld]]''.<ref name="McCarthy1992">{{cite book|last=McCarthy|first=Robert E.|title=Secrets of Hollywood Special Effects|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=B4applRToVQC&pg=PA101|year=1992|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-240-80108-7|page=101}}</ref>
* '''Mike Tristano''': Owner and Founder of Mike Tristano & Co.; Credits include ''[[Top Shot]]'' and ''[[Triggers: Weapons That Changed the World]]''<ref name="Kobler2005">{{cite book|last=Kobler|first=Helmut|title=Anatomy Of A Guerrilla Film: The Making Of Radius|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=w50bAQAAIAAJ|year=2005|publisher=Thomson Course Technology|isbn=978-1-59200-910-7|pages=102–103}}</ref>
* '''Jeremy E. Goldstein''': Rostered armorer at Tristano & Co.; He's the youngest professionally working entertainment armorer in the United States. Film and TV credits include ''[[Laid in America]]'', ''[[imdbtitle:7061270|Called and Chosen]], [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7703976/?ref_=fn_al_tt_2 Grayson], Medal of Honor (series),'' and ''The Casket Lake Anthology.'' 
